Let's construct the fixed version:

```java
static boolean isSimpleNumber(String s) {
    int len = s.length();
    if (len == 0) {
      return false;
    }
    if (s.charAt(0) == '0' && len > 1) {
      return false;
    }
    for (int index = 0; index < len; index++) {
      char c = s.charAt(index);
      if (c < '0' || c > '9') {
        return false;
      }
    }
    return true;
}
```

This adds check for leading zero and also early return for empty string (though the loop would also return false). It also returns true after loop, because we already know len > 0.

